pr_body:
This is an experimental branch to support decorators preserving iscoroutinefunction (if the caller is a coroutine) and not preserving it (if the caller is a regular function). This was requested by Itaï Ben Yaacov. For instance now

```python
@decorator
def coro_to_func(coro, *args, **kw):
    "Convert a coroutine into a function"
    return get_event_loop().run_until_complete(coro(*args, **kw))
```

works as you would expect.

This is an extraction of the forced lists feature of #104.
@martinblech requested to split #104 in smaller pull requests, and as I need
this feature, here it is.

eg:if old_change.attributes.index() == change.attributes.index() and old_change.nlri.nexthop.index() == change.nlri.nexthop.index():
AttributeError: 'IPSelf' object has no attribute 'index'
not certain if this is the right thing to do although it does seem to work in my environment. this diff is more to point out the issue i've seen and to suggest a possible fix

